<p><a name="Special_education_and_homeschooling" id="Special_education_and_homeschooling"></a></p>
<h3><span class="editsection">[<a href="/w/index.php?title=Waldorf_education&amp;action=edit&amp;section=33" title="Edit section: Special education and homeschooling">edit</a>]</span> <span class="mw-headline">Special education and homeschooling</span></h3>
<ul>
<li><a href="http://www.camphill.org.uk/" class="external text" title="http://www.camphill.org.uk/" rel="nofollow">Camphill Communities</a> are intentional communities of people with disabilities that recognize the potential, dignity, spiritual integrity and contributions of each individual.</li>
<li><a href="http://www.mothersnature.com/toddlers/info/waldorfhome.html" class="external text" title="http://www.mothersnature.com/toddlers/info/waldorfhome.html" rel="nofollow">The Future of Waldorf Homeschooling</a> article by Barbara Dewey at Mother's Nature web site</li>
<li><a href="http://www.waldorffamilynetwork.com/homeschooling.html" class="external text" title="http://www.waldorffamilynetwork.com/homeschooling.html" rel="nofollow">Waldorf homeschooling resource directory</a> by Waldorf Family Network</li>
</ul>
